      <section id="summary-tables" class="paper-section">
        <header class="section-header">
          <h1 class="section-title">Disease Detection Summary</h1>
        </header>
        <div class="paper-content">

<p>The tables below summarize the current state of machine learning models that detect disease from routine blood tests (CBC and CMP panels) already collected at annual physicals. The research covers 25 diseases: 13 cancers and 12 non-cancer conditions.</p>

<p>Four algorithms have reached clinical deployment. ColonFlag for colorectal cancer is live in Israel, the US, and the UK. LungFlag for lung cancer has completed large-scale validation at Kaiser Permanente. Klinrisk for chronic kidney disease received CE-mark from Roche for its navify platform in October 2025. TREWS for sepsis is deployed across five Johns Hopkins hospitals with a demonstrated 18.7% mortality reduction.</p>

